t the Otherworld and their views about women in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFantasy in literature. 0aIrish literaturexHistory and criticismyTo 1100. 0aWomen in literature. 4aGender and Sexuality Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aLiterary Theory, Criticism, and History. 4aMedieval Studies. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Ireland.2bisacsh  aEarly Ireland, Women, the Otherworld, Supernatural.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048555987?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048555987423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048555987/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023